)AREA MXIHAREA
!Function
+  Controls MXI screen attributes for specific panel elements.
+  You can also specify if the ISPF 'Tab to Point and Shoot' setting
+  is to be forced 'ON' when MXI is invoked.
+
!Force tab to point and shoot fields
+  When selected, this causes MXI to set on the ISPF 'Tab to point and s
+  setting. When MXI is terminated, it will reset this ISPF setting to i
+  previous value. This setting only applies to users who have NOT set t
+  'Tab to point and shoot fields' in their ISPF settings.
+  Note that changes to this setting take effect on the next invocation
+  of MXI.
+
!Colour
+  This specifies the colour of the field. This can be one of the
+  following values :
+  ÖRED
+  ÖYELLOW
+  ÖWHITE
+  ÖGREEN
+  ÖTURQ
+  ÖBLUE
+  ÖPINK
+
!Highlight
+  This specifies the highlighting attribute for the field. This can be
+  one of the following values :
+  ÖNORMAL      + No special attributes.
+  ÖUSCORE      + The field is underlined.
+  ÖBLINK       + The field will blink.
+  ÖREVERSE     + The field will be displayed in reverse video.
+
!Intensity
+  This specifies the intensity of the field. This can be one of the
+  following values :
+  ÖLOW         + Low intensity.
+  ÖHIGH        + High intensity.
+
)INIT
